reated_at":"2026-03-02T06:45:23.000-06:00","title":"APT Graph Colouring","url":"https://github.com/RyanGibb/apt-graph-colouring","score":5,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"ryangibb","user_is_author":true,"tags":["compsci","show"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7fdbnh","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/7fdbnh/apt_graph_colouring"},{"short_id":"fztjyg","created_at":"2026-03-02T06:26:44.000-06:00","title":"Narwhal v0.5.0 – pub/sub messaging server, now powered by io_uring","url":"https://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0","score":5,"flags":2,"comment_count":1,"description":"\u003cp\u003ehi again! i'm back with a new release of Narwhal, the lightweight pub/sub server i shared a while ago. the biggest change in v0.5.0 is the migration from tokio to monoio as the primary async runtime, which means the server now runs entirely on io_uring on Linux:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ehttps://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethe project is still alpha, but the core is getting more solid with each release. would love feedback, especially from anyone who has experience tuning io_uring-based servers. i'm sure there's still a lot of room to squeeze more out of it. :)\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"hi again! i'm back with a new release of Narwhal, the lightweight pub/sub server i shared a while ago. the biggest change in v0.5.0 is the migration from tokio to monoio as the primary async runtime, which means the server now runs entirely on io_uring on Linux:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/narwhal-io/narwhal/releases/tag/narwhal-0.5.0\r\n\r\nthe project is still alpha, but the core is getting more solid with each release. would love feedback, especially from anyone who has experience tuning io_uring-based servers. i'm sure there's still a lot of room to squeeze more out of it. :)","submitter_user":"ortuman","user_is_author":true,"tags":["distributed","linux","performance","programming","rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fztjyg","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fztjyg/narwhal_v0_5_0_pub_sub_messaging_server_now"},{"short_id":"bp15oz","created_at":"2026-03-02T05:44:12.000-06:00","title":"Kovan: From Production MVCC Systems to Wait-Free Memory Reclamation","url":"https://vertexclique.com/blog/kovan-from-prod-to-mr/","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"sp6370","user_is_author":false,"tags":["formalmethods","rust"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bp15oz","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/bp15oz/kovan_from_production_mvcc_systems_wait"}]